properties.assessment_comment: Numerous spawning sockeye immediately adjacent to culvert outlet and upstream. properties.assessment_comment: Review of flood plane mapping indicates that this watershed actually drains to 1 km West through an open bottom structure. Adjacent land use is for cattle so this may be affecting drainage and habitat health upstream.
properties.condition_notes: Pipe is rusted all the way through at the top 1 m
properties.climate_notes: This cover is not appear to be the main drain for this watershed. Evaluation of floodplain mapping indicates this watershed drains through the larger open bottom of structure located approximately 1 km west.
properties.climate_priority_notes: Psycho spawning area identified to the west 1 km and five value Medina River just downstream, however does not seem likely that this crossing receives much flow indicated by the type and size Channell

properties.climate_notes: Cover appears undersized, however there appears to be a decent buffer distance between here and the likely high value habitat, located downstream in the Nadina river with no infrastructure in between
